<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-05-17a.48.0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100549" speakername="Lord Rooker" colon=":" colnum="48"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/60517w05.htm#60517w05_spnew0">
	<p pid="a.48.0/1">Since the Northern Ireland (Sentences) Act 1998 came into force on <phrase class="date" code="1998-04-10">10 April 1998</phrase> the number of persons who have had their licences suspended and been recalled to prison in each year under this legislation and the numbers of those charged and convicted of offences are as shown in the table below. (This is out of a total of 448 persons who have been released early on their sentences under the Act).</p>
	<table>
		<tbody>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/4"> <td>Year</td> <td>Number Recalled</td> <td>Charged</td> <td>Not Charged</td> <td>Number Convicted</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/5"> <td>1998</td> <td>0</td> <td>0</td> <td>0</td> <td>0</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/6"> <td>1999</td> <td>0</td> <td>0</td> <td>0</td> <td>0</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/7"> <td>2000</td> <td>2</td> <td>1</td> <td>1</td> <td>1</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/8"> <td>2001</td> <td>3</td> <td>2</td> <td>1</td> <td>2</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/9"> <td>2002</td> <td>2</td> <td>2</td> <td>0</td> <td>2</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/10"> <td>2003</td> <td>2</td> <td>1</td> <td>1</td> <td>1</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/11"> <td>2004</td> <td>1</td> <td>1</td> <td>0</td> <td>1</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/12"> <td>2005</td> <td>5</td> <td>*3</td> <td>2</td> <td>*2</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/13"> <td>2006##</td> <td>1</td> <td>*1</td> <td>0</td> <td>*0</td> </tr>
			<tr pid="a.48.0/14"> <td>Totals</td> <td>16</td> <td>11</td> <td>5</td> <td>9</td> </tr>
